26:53.195 --> 26:56.782
He'd already ripped me off
for, you know, 400 bucks,

26:56.823 --> 26:58.867
taken my debit card,

26:58.909 --> 27:01.161
<i>and he drove to the top of that overpass</i>

27:01.203 --> 27:03.663
<i>which was just a two-minute drive.</i>

27:03.705 --> 27:06.500
<i>He got out of the car, he
walked across the street,</i>

27:06.542 --> 27:08.668
to the south-bound side,

27:08.710 --> 27:11.629
took off his sandals and dove head first.

27:11.671 --> 27:13.257
[reporter] <i> Ian Mautner's autopsy report</i>

27:13.299 --> 27:16.218
<i>showed an unknown amount of
what's called mitragynine,</i>

27:16.260 --> 27:18.095
<i>the active ingredient in kratom.</i>

27:18.137 --> 27:20.638
<i>Also listed, a number of antidepressants.</i>

27:20.680 --> 27:23.016
<i>Linda believes it was Ian's addiction
to kratom</i>

27:23.058 --> 27:25.060
<i>that ultimately sent him over the edge.</i>

27:25.102 --> 27:27.229
[Mautner] <i>He was the kind of kid</i>
<i>that I could trust.</i>

27:27.271 --> 27:29.773
<i>He always told me everything.</i>

27:29.815 --> 27:31.900
<i>- We were super, super close.</i>
- [Chris] <i> Mm-hmm.</i>

27:31.942 --> 27:34.445
<i>And he invited me to the kava bar.</i>

27:34.487 --> 27:38.532
He was spending a lot of money there,
like about 50 bucks a day.

27:38.574 --> 27:41.118
<i>And when I went there, I
didn't know what kratom was.</i>

27:41.160 --> 27:42.744
<i>You know, I had a drink...</i>

27:42.786 --> 27:44.955
<i>A couple of times I went down there
and had a drink.</i>

27:44.997 --> 27:47.416
I actually called my sponsor

27:47.458 --> 27:50.752
and I said, "You know, I tried this stuff.
Ian's doing this a lot."

27:50.794 --> 27:52.546
And she said, "You need to be careful,

27:52.588 --> 27:54.798
you know, because that doesn't sound good."

27:54.840 --> 27:57.675
- So, how long have you been sober for?
- For 22 years now.

27:57.717 --> 27:59.470
- Congratulations. That's amazing.
- Thanks.

27:59.512 --> 28:03.015
And I said, "Ian, if you're doing drugs,
this is really bad",

28:03.056 --> 28:05.434
because it can trigger the brain,

28:05.476 --> 28:10.147
and set off things, you know, like
bipolar disorder or schizophrenia.

28:10.189 --> 28:12.358
And he said, "Mom, I'm not doing drugs."

28:12.399 --> 28:16.529
You know, and it was... It became like
fighting that was going on between us.

28:16.570 --> 28:20.115
I mean, he'd spend hours in the bathroom
picking his face,

28:20.157 --> 28:22.451
and one time the mirror even came off.

28:22.493 --> 28:25.912
You know, the bathroom wall detached.

28:25.954 --> 28:28.290
And why do you think he was picking his face?
Like, what was he doing?

28:28.332 --> 28:30.209
We thought it was meth.

28:30.250 --> 28:32.628
Like, sometimes he'd be so sedated

28:32.670 --> 28:35.631
that his eyes would roll back in his head.

28:35.673 --> 28:38.967
And he'd talk to me and he'd go, "Mother..."

28:39.009 --> 28:41.512
<i>- You know, and he'd nod off.</i>
- [Chris] <i> Yeah.</i>

28:41.554 --> 28:44.890
<i>- And that sounds more like a heroin...</i>
- [Mautner] Heroin...

28:44.931 --> 28:48.435
<i>Nodding off on, like, pills or something
like that. That's kinda very similar.</i>

28:48.477 --> 28:51.813
More important, you know,
important for parents,

28:51.855 --> 28:55.234
- he was on medication as well, right, for...
- Yes.

28:55.275 --> 28:59.154
- Psychological issues, right? So...
- Yes.

28:59.196 --> 29:02.408
If you're on medication and you're taking
something that affects your brain,

29:02.449 --> 29:06.161
then we're really, you know, kinda playing
Russian roulette there.

29:06.203 --> 29:08.830
You don't know what you're
getting into at all.

29:08.872 --> 29:12.251
I've been accused of everything,
from, you know, on blogs,

29:12.292 --> 29:15.462
from kicking my son out of the house
because he was gay.

29:16.213 --> 29:19.341
You know, that's...

29:19.383 --> 29:23.887
What's that got to do with it, you know?
That came out in therapy.

29:23.929 --> 29:26.806
This was a different person.
This was addiction.

29:26.848 --> 29:30.102
This was living in my house,
and I couldn't have that.

29:30.143 --> 29:33.146
You don't put any other stuff in your drink?

29:33.188 --> 29:36.024
- It's kava and kratom, right?
- It's as raw as you get.

29:36.066 --> 29:39.695
Because Linda Mautner told me that you guys
lace the drinks.

29:39.737 --> 29:43.532
And that's what made her son, you know,
jump off a bridge to commit suicide,

29:43.574 --> 29:46.034
which is a very tragic story.

29:46.076 --> 29:48.995
Well, Linda Mautner is consistently incorrect.

29:49.037 --> 29:53.125
<i>I knew him personally. I just see a mother
trying to make sense</i>

29:53.166 --> 29:56.795
<i>- out of something senseless. It doesn't make sense.</i>
- [Chris] <i> Yeah.</i>

29:56.836 --> 29:59.172
[Scianno] <i> But his cause
of death wasn't kratom.</i>

29:59.214 --> 30:01.508
She gets to go on the news,

30:01.550 --> 30:04.553
you know, sympathetic media, for
whatever reason, I don't know.

30:04.595 --> 30:06.680
I don't know whose behind it, or what.

30:06.722 --> 30:10.142
- But she gets to say whatever she wants to say.
- Mm-hmm.

30:10.183 --> 30:12.770
And you know, it's out there.

30:12.811 --> 30:15.397
So, kratom has a PR problem.

30:15.439 --> 30:21.779
Look, she told us... She was like,
"Well, you know, he died from kratom."

30:21.820 --> 30:25.574
"Uh, you sure?" Well, the first time
he checked into drug rehab,

30:25.616 --> 30:27.867
he had opioids in his system,

30:27.909 --> 30:30.412
the second time he checked into drug rehab,

30:30.454 --> 30:33.749
he had methamphetamines in his system.

30:33.791 --> 30:35.584
And he jumped off a bridge and killed himself.

30:35.626 --> 30:39.254
I mean, God bless her, but it's like, "Ma'am,

30:39.296 --> 30:41.923
your son didn't die from kratom."

30:41.965 --> 30:44.843
I went from smoking a
pack of cigarettes a day,

30:44.884 --> 30:47.971
drinking 20 Red Bulls a day,
doing 90 pain pills a day,

30:48.013 --> 30:50.265
<i>snorting seven grams of cocaine a day,</i>

30:50.307 --> 30:51.809
<i>banging a ton of porn stars a day...</i>

30:51.850 --> 30:54.894
I don't want to do anything, none of that.

30:54.936 --> 30:59.483
But, here's the thing, I am in so much pain
when I wake up.

30:59.525 --> 31:01.234
<i>But then I found kratom.</i>

31:01.276 --> 31:06.281
And my pain level, like I said,
went from a nine to a three.

31:06.323 --> 31:09.785
<i>There was an infant born with total addiction,</i>

31:09.827 --> 31:11.453
<i>so they were in withdrawal,</i>

31:11.495 --> 31:16.082
And the mother said the only thing that
she had ingested

31:16.124 --> 31:17.626
was the kratom.

31:17.668 --> 31:20.629
<i>But luckily, she had some of her kratom
with her.</i>

31:20.671 --> 31:22.798
<i>And so, they sent a sample to us,</i>

31:22.840 --> 31:26.218
and we found that the actual kratom sample

31:26.259 --> 31:29.429
was adulterated with the hydrocodone.

31:29.471 --> 31:32.349
I mean, in Sweden, there was definitely
a bunch of deaths

31:32.391 --> 31:35.728
because of this laced product
with O-Desmethyltramadol,

31:35.769 --> 31:38.605
which is a very potent synthetic opioid.

31:38.647 --> 31:40.566
And it seems pretty clear

31:40.607 --> 31:43.109
that the deaths are from that component,
and not from the Kratom itself.

31:43.151 --> 31:45.779
He has not died because of kratom,
you see. As I said just now,

31:45.821 --> 31:49.282
people have been using kratom in
Southeast Asia for more than 100 years.

31:49.324 --> 31:51.201
There have not been any mortality cases.

31:51.243 --> 31:53.871
Nobody has died using Kratom in Malaysia.

31:53.912 --> 31:57.207
The only deaths listed

31:57.249 --> 32:02.421
as associated with kratom
are polydrug situations,

32:02.462 --> 32:05.883
where a person was on multiple other illicit

32:05.924 --> 32:08.635
and/or prescription drugs when they died.

32:08.677 --> 32:11.597
It's not new, it's not synthetic.

32:11.638 --> 32:14.140
And the media is attaching onto this as new.

32:14.182 --> 32:17.728
<i>It's new to the United
States in the last 20 years,</i>

32:17.770 --> 32:19.396
<i>but it's been used in Southeast Asia</i>

32:19.438 --> 32:22.107
<i>over hundreds and thousands
of years, culturally,</i>

32:22.148 --> 32:23.567
<i>for medicinal purposes.</i>

32:23.609 --> 32:25.819
<i>And yet, here we have the DEA</i>

32:25.861 --> 32:29.155
<i>saying that there's no medicinal use
from this plant,</i>

32:29.197 --> 32:34.453
when every single one of our members
is getting medicinal benefit...

32:34.494 --> 32:36.204
What is the problem with kratom?

32:36.246 --> 32:39.999
Why is it so controversial? Why are
people so up in arms about it?

32:40.041 --> 32:41.919
That could go in so many different directions.

32:41.960 --> 32:44.880
And I think primarily what the problem is,

32:44.922 --> 32:47.006
it is competition

32:47.048 --> 32:52.220
<i>to some of the largest money-making industries
in the United States.</i>

32:52.262 --> 32:55.390
And I think that with the
media and the propaganda

32:55.432 --> 32:58.435
that they've been allowed
to spew to the public,

32:58.477 --> 33:00.103
which is based on exaggeration.

33:00.145 --> 33:04.733
People are believing that it is something
like illegal heroin,

33:04.775 --> 33:10.363
which is, to me, the biggest joke,
and yet, the saddest joke

33:10.405 --> 33:11.531
that I've ever heard.

33:11.573 --> 33:13.992
It's not the kind of thing that you crave

33:14.033 --> 33:16.995
and you feel like you have to go out
and seek.

33:17.036 --> 33:21.207
Because it's not the kind of thing
that you can escape your life from.

33:21.249 --> 33:23.877
That's the major difference to me.

33:23.919 --> 33:27.046
When I was on opioids, I
was using them to escape.

33:27.088 --> 33:29.508
It was a miserable existence.

33:29.549 --> 33:33.011
I was in my 30s. All my friends were getting
married and having children,

33:33.052 --> 33:36.181
I never was able to have children.
I was sick for ten years.

33:36.222 --> 33:41.770
We are people that just want a natural
alternative to prescription drugs.

33:41.812 --> 33:43.396
And this is what works for us.

33:43.438 --> 33:46.733
Also, interestingly, about 60% of our members

33:46.775 --> 33:49.569
have never even experienced
addiction in their lives.

33:49.611 --> 33:55.283
<i>They're just looking for an alternative
to pain medications.</i>

33:55.325 --> 33:57.703
[Chris] <i> I figured if I'm going
to continue to use kratom,</i>

33:57.744 --> 34:00.413
<i>I should probably consult with the people
that matter the most.</i>

34:00.455 --> 34:05.043
<i>My brother Smelly recently started using
kratom as a pre-workout supplement.</i>

34:05.084 --> 34:08.213
[Smelly] <i> I like it, and I like the
feeling of it. It felt pretty good.</i>

34:08.254 --> 34:09.840
[Chris] <i> What kind of feeling
do you get from it?</i>

34:09.882 --> 34:13.342
It just kind of almost gave me,
like, a sense of calmness,

34:13.385 --> 34:16.346
and maybe a little bit better focus even.

34:16.388 --> 34:18.097
Yeah, I wanted you guys to try it

34:18.139 --> 34:21.141
because I didn't want anybody to be scared
of what I was taking.

34:21.184 --> 34:23.061
- Like, it was one of the main reasons...
- Right.

34:23.101 --> 34:27.440
Uh, has it ever caused any
concern for you, or...

34:27.482 --> 34:30.235
It doesn't seem that powerful

34:30.275 --> 34:34.197
to have a negative impact on your life.

34:34.239 --> 34:35.949
You know, I guess that's what
we're talking about here

34:35.991 --> 34:38.201
when we're talking about addiction,

34:38.243 --> 34:40.786
like who cares if you're addicted
to lifting weights

34:40.829 --> 34:42.748
if it doesn't hurt anybody else.

34:42.789 --> 34:46.043
[Chris] <i> When you hurt your elbow,
you're kind of, you know, beat up.</i>

34:46.083 --> 34:47.585
<i>How do you cope with pain?</i>

34:47.627 --> 34:50.047
I usually just, I mean, I
usually just deal with it.

34:50.088 --> 34:53.884
You know, so, for now, I'm trying to actually,
like, listen to the doctors and stuff,

34:53.926 --> 34:56.219
and use my arm a little bit less.

34:56.261 --> 34:59.097
And try not to do any upper body exercises
at all.

34:59.138 --> 35:00.974
<i>You know, as long as I get back
to it at some point,</i>

35:01.016 --> 35:02.350
<i>it is what I love to do.</i>

35:02.392 --> 35:04.519
So, whether I have to have
a surgery or whatever,

35:04.561 --> 35:06.271
I'll deal with it at that point.

35:06.312 --> 35:09.066
You know, I've had one knee replacement,
two hip replacements.

35:09.148 --> 35:12.277
They've been fine, I have no problem.
I was riding my bike,

35:12.318 --> 35:15.614
between five and seven miles a day, you know,
and everything.

35:15.655 --> 35:18.909
And as I was going to hand a
guy a bag, I trip over a curb,

35:18.951 --> 35:21.661
and I get this groin pull somehow.

35:21.703 --> 35:23.789
<i>They gave me some hydrocodone
to take, you know.</i>

35:23.830 --> 35:25.624
<i>And that was helping.</i>

35:25.665 --> 35:27.876
<i>I'd take two in the morning, two
in the afternoon, two at night,</i>

35:27.918 --> 35:29.920
<i>but it was still really painful.</i>

35:29.962 --> 35:33.548
<i>Then you had given me some kratom, I think
it was... I can't remember exactly,</i>

35:33.590 --> 35:38.303
but from April on, I was fine. I
wasn't taking the hydrocodone anymore.

35:38.344 --> 35:39.930
I was taking that,

35:39.972 --> 35:41.807
and I was back to riding my bike.
I rode my bike all summer.

35:41.848 --> 35:44.851
And so, I've been taking two a day,

35:44.893 --> 35:46.144
it doesn't make me high.

35:46.185 --> 35:48.730
<i>I don't realize that I took it.</i>

35:48.772 --> 35:50.899
<i>But I'm always happy, I'm
always in a good mood.</i>

35:50.941 --> 35:54.736
<i>I've never really been a person
that was depressed or anything.</i>

35:54.778 --> 35:56.613
I mean, I hate to be cynical,

35:56.655 --> 35:59.616
but like everything in this country
is run by money.

35:59.658 --> 36:01.576
The government's not going
to do their research,

36:01.618 --> 36:04.245
and the pharmaceutical companies
aren't going to do the research,

36:04.287 --> 36:05.914
unless there's something in it for them.

36:05.956 --> 36:07.833
If there's something in it for the government,
they'll do it.

36:07.874 --> 36:10.209
If there's something in it for the
pharmaceutical companies, they'll do it.

36:10.251 --> 36:12.963
But if there's nothing in it for either
one of them, they won't put up the money.

36:13.005 --> 36:14.673
So, if you come up with something like that,

36:14.714 --> 36:16.466
you've got to come up with the studies.

36:16.508 --> 36:17.926
What do you have going on with you?

36:17.968 --> 36:19.928
Well, it's an entrapped nerve in my back

36:19.970 --> 36:22.848
that's making the pain go all the way down
into my leg,

36:22.889 --> 36:26.018
make me lose movement in my leg.

36:26.059 --> 36:29.395
And it's, like, 24/7 pain.

36:29.437 --> 36:32.941
Unless I'm sleeping, I don't know I have...
I don't have any pain.

36:32.983 --> 36:34.943
<i>Other than that, I have pain all the time.</i>

36:34.985 --> 36:38.030
<i>And I don't think people shouldn't
try something for pain.</i>

36:38.071 --> 36:41.574
<i>I just don't think they should take
more than they should.</i>

36:41.616 --> 36:43.994
And I think all of it, the kratom and all,

36:44.036 --> 36:45.244
I think they're trying to stop it

36:45.286 --> 36:47.622
because they're probably trying to make it,

36:47.664 --> 36:49.124
so they can sell it and make money.

36:49.166 --> 36:50.917
Why are you afraid to try it?

36:52.335 --> 36:55.296
- For pain? Um...
- Mm-hmm.

36:55.338 --> 36:59.968
I don't know, I just, I just never tried
any kind of...

37:00.010 --> 37:01.511
anything, and so...

37:01.553 --> 37:03.722
But if the doctor gave
it to you, you'd try it?

37:04.597 --> 37:06.391
I probably would.

37:06.432 --> 37:08.852
[Chris] <i> So, my mom was afraid to take Kratom.</i>

37:08.894 --> 37:10.770
<i>But my friend's mom didn't hesitate.</i>

37:10.812 --> 37:12.647
<i>This is Tony from the gym.</i>

37:12.689 --> 37:15.859
<i>His mother started taking kratom
to get off her hydrocodone,</i>

37:15.901 --> 37:18.570
<i>and a lot of the other pills
she's been prescribed.</i>

37:18.611 --> 37:20.739
- [Chris] You're 89 years old, huh?
- Yeah.

37:20.780 --> 37:22.949
- You look fantastic.
- Well, thank you.

37:22.991 --> 37:25.326
- Like a spring chicken, 89 years old, come on.
- [laughs]

37:25.368 --> 37:26.995
[Mrs. Porter] <i>Some days I feel like it.</i>

37:27.037 --> 37:29.998
- [Chris] <i> You started taking kratom recently, huh?</i>
<i>- Yes.</i>

37:30.040 --> 37:32.500
- Because I'm on a lot of medicines.
- I'm all ears.

37:32.542 --> 37:35.628
I'm on about 15 different medicines.

37:35.670 --> 37:37.964
<i>Levothyroxine,</i>

37:38.006 --> 37:40.926
<i>Benecol, Amlodipine,</i>

37:40.967 --> 37:43.970
<i>hydrochloride, hydrocodone,</i>

37:44.012 --> 37:46.973
<i>Prezolon, take calcium,</i>

37:47.015 --> 37:50.060
<i>the Prolia injection, twice a year.</i>

37:50.102 --> 37:53.813
I don't know a lot of people who
take as much medicine as I do.

37:53.855 --> 37:57.150
I have a sister, 91, and
she takes six pills day.

37:57.192 --> 38:00.445
- I'm just tired of pain.
- [Chris] Yeah.

38:00.486 --> 38:04.449
And if anything else can help me,

38:04.490 --> 38:08.036
<i>without me taking all of these medicines,
you know, I'd try.</i>

38:08.078 --> 38:11.248
[Chris] The DEA is trying to
make it a Schedule I drug.

38:11.289 --> 38:13.792
You know, on par with heroin,
and these other drugs.

38:13.833 --> 38:17.420
But, you've taken it, you don't
see it that way, do you?

38:17.462 --> 38:20.673
- Doesn't make you high?
- No, no.

38:20.715 --> 38:22.968
I do what I want to do.

38:23.009 --> 38:25.637
- Like always.
- [Chris] What kind of stuff do you do every day?

38:25.678 --> 38:27.430
Everything I want to.

38:27.472 --> 38:31.601
If it's nice outside, I'm outside in the yard
or whatever,

38:31.643 --> 38:34.395
<i>because if I'm just sitting, it's worse.</i>

38:34.437 --> 38:39.276
<i>If I move around or whatever,
then, you know, I feel better.</i>

38:39.317 --> 38:42.237
- [Chris] <i> If you're moving, you're not in pain?</i>
<i>- I'm in pain, yeah.</i>

38:42.279 --> 38:47.242
But I just learn to... I just don't
give into all of it.

38:47.284 --> 38:49.869
[Chris] <i> When the government tries
to ban something people want,</i>

38:49.911 --> 38:53.123
<i>the people band together
and march on Washington.</i>

38:53.165 --> 38:56.417
<i>Kratom advocates were able to get
120,000 people</i>

38:56.459 --> 38:59.587
<i>to sign a petition to keep Kratom legal.</i>

38:59.629 --> 39:02.590
<i>This march was the last-ditch effort
to get the DEA</i>

39:02.632 --> 39:05.343
<i>to put the brakes on a Schedule I ban.</i>

39:05.384 --> 39:07.846
- [cheering]
- We are Kratom!

39:07.887 --> 39:10.556
[all chanting] We are Kratom!

39:10.598 --> 39:14.477
[Chris] <i> When I went out to DC for the
Kratom march, I didn't know what to expect.</i>

39:14.519 --> 39:17.772
<i>But I met some very fascinating people
from all walks of life.</i>

39:17.814 --> 39:21.151
<i>And we had one thing in common, pain.</i>

39:21.193 --> 39:22.819
What do you guys hope comes out of this?

39:22.861 --> 39:25.571
That I get to keep Kratom in my life,
because it saved my life.

39:25.613 --> 39:27.240
I was pretty much suicidal

39:27.282 --> 39:29.326
<i>before my doctor... I went in there suicidal.</i>

39:29.367 --> 39:31.870
<i>I got pregnant actually, and I was sent
to the methadone clinic,</i>

39:31.911 --> 39:33.997
I had to have my daughter on methadone,

39:34.039 --> 39:38.543
which was a complete disaster pretty much.

39:38.584 --> 39:40.545
<i>It's a very emotional subject for me,</i>

39:40.586 --> 39:42.547
<i>I watched my daughter go through withdrawal
for six months afterwards.</i>

39:42.588 --> 39:48.136
