<i>and obliterated the AIDS epidemic.</i>

01:13:20.271 --> 01:13:24.234
<i>Why aren't we doing the same
for the opioid epidemic?</i>

01:13:24.275 --> 01:13:28.279
<i>But I called the DEA, the FDA, and the NIDA,</i>

01:13:28.321 --> 01:13:30.365
<i>and they all said the same thing,</i>

01:13:30.406 --> 01:13:32.449
<i>"We're not gonna talk to you."</i>

01:13:32.491 --> 01:13:35.411
<i>So, it's time to take
matters into our own hands.</i>

01:13:35.452 --> 01:13:38.206
<i>First, we're gonna need
some money for research.</i>

01:13:38.248 --> 01:13:40.791
[Chris] <i> You know, Dr. McCurdy
was with us in England</i>

01:13:40.833 --> 01:13:42.752
<i>and he came out with all this new research.</i>

01:13:42.793 --> 01:13:45.671
And he's saying, you know, the real thing
that we need is money for research.

01:13:45.713 --> 01:13:47.798
And you've done really well with kratom.

01:13:47.840 --> 01:13:51.761
I just keep thinking like, "Man, if all
these other companies keep bombing out,

01:13:51.802 --> 01:13:54.847
they're not testing our product, they're
not doing what they're supposed to do,

01:13:54.889 --> 01:13:56.640
like, we can do it."

01:13:56.682 --> 01:13:59.143
[Dunn] The other thing I like that
McCurdy's doing is he's developing

01:13:59.185 --> 01:14:01.687
that quick and easy test for adulterants.

01:14:01.729 --> 01:14:05.024
So if their people are not testing the
product, and the product is dirty,

01:14:05.066 --> 01:14:06.984
he's got it. He's developing
that test for that as well.

01:14:07.026 --> 01:14:10.321
So, when, like, when I did <i>Prescription Thugs,</i>
it was a different thing.

01:14:10.363 --> 01:14:11.781
So I did <i> Prescription Thugs,</i>

01:14:11.822 --> 01:14:13.783
I wanted to help people get off of opioids.

01:14:13.824 --> 01:14:19.080
And I think that we achieved warning people
that opioids are dangerous.

01:14:19.122 --> 01:14:22.499
